"n.转矩；项圈 【英】 n.转矩(a force that produces rotation or torsion) 【考】 torque : rotation / tension : elongation(力矩使旋转/张力使 伸长) 【记】 torq(转)+ue→转矩→ 造成东西旋转的力量 n. 转矩(一种产生扭转趋势的力的单位) 【记】tor转, que－转矩 【类】torque: rotation = tension: elongation转矩使旋转 = 张力使伸长 【记】源自tort- 扭曲，扭转；音：头盔，头盔就像项圈戴在脖子上，头转来转去；音：套圈(que 读汉语拼音)，套圈时需要转矩使之旋转；torque是转矩，torch 火炬，也有个炬，对torch施加转矩，一扭其项圈就出火 【相关】torsion 扭转，转矩 torque (n.)  ""rotating force,"" 1882, from Latin torquere ""to twist, turn, turn about, twist awry, distort, torture,"" from PIE *torkw-eyo-, causative of *terkw- ""to twist"" (see thwart (adv.)). The word also is used (since 1834) by antiquarians and others as a term for the twisted metal necklace worn anciently by Gauls, Britons, Germans, etc., from Latin torques ""collar of twisted metal,"" from torquere. Earlier it had been called in English torques (1690s). Torque-wrench is from 1941. torque (v.)  1570s (implied in torqued ""twisted""), from torque (n.)."
